result.execSummary:
The defendant Deion D Jones was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Deion D Jones is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Deion D Jones was found guilty of Criminal Damage to Property, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.01(1).
  • Deion D Jones was found guilty of Theft-Movable Property <=$2500 [Modifiers: Penalties for Misdemeanors-Class "A"], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.20(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: REQUEST TO ISSUE CIVIL JUDGMENT FOR OUTSTANDING RESTITUTION RECEIVED AND FORWARDED TO ALI. OS

Defendant Deion D Jones in court with attorney Awni M Yasin.  Patrick J Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy court clerk:  vk  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant. 
As to Count 2:  The Court sentenced the defendant to serve 6 MONTHS at the House of Corrections straight time with 2 days credit.
As to Count 3:  The Court sentenced the defendant to serve 6 MONTHS at the House of Corrections straight time concurrent to Count 2.
The sentences are  CONSECUTIVEto any other sentence.

Court STAYED the sentence and placed the defendant on 1 YEAR probation.
  Conditions of Probation:
- No further violations rising to the level of probable cause
- Cooperate with the Probation Department
- No possession of weapons
- 50 hours of community service
- No contact with the victim
- Write a letter of apology to Terrance I within 30 days
- Provide a DNA sample. if one has not been provided
- Fulltime work and/or school
- Obtain HSED/GED

Court ordered the defendant pay all of the following by the end of supervision.  Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment:
Restitution in the amount of $1050.00 to Terrance I. 
Pay DNA surcharges;
Court waives all other court costs given his age 
-  No Cash Bail Posted 

Court advised defendant of his right to seek postconviction relief.

Filed:  
Crime Victim Impact Statement
Ineligible Voting Notice and Acknowledgement
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief
Pretrial Incarceration Credit

Court will consider motion for expungement if defendant successfully completes probation including full payment of restitution  and obtaining a high school diploma.

Defendant Deion D Jones in court with attorney Awni M Yasin.  Patrick J Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy court clerk:  vk  As to Counts 2 & 3:  Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, plead GUILTY and was examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis for the plea.  Defendant further advised that if he is not a US citizen deportation is possible.  Court found defendant guilty as charged in the Information and ordered entry of Judgment of Conviction.  
Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon he may never possess a firearm.  Court advised defendant that his voting rights are suspended, and may not vote in any election until his civil rights are restored.
As to Count 1:  Pursuant to negotiations and on State's motion Court dismissed the count.
Court ordered case adjourned for sentencing in Branch  19.  Status hearing scheduled for August 31, 2015 at 08:30 am.
